{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1772200774,"nonce":"eYBTdcaHr0htZg25JLsp18PvEGc=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87ufQ8azwAAAAVjEsCL"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772201362,"nonce":"AyNDnOuYlY8DZ6I8Dr/FWa4bP0s=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87s0YfA","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/305#issuecomment-3973154752"},"message":"## Review\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** Yes — Three files, each getting a 2-4 line addition. Clean single-PR scope.\n\n**Right repo?** Yes — All three target files (`.agent/instructions/gemini-cli.instructions.md`, `.github/copilot-instructions.md`, `.agent/AGENT_ONBOARDING.md`) live in the workspace repo.\n\n**Dependencies**: None identified. The skills already exist; this is purely a discovery improvement.\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Primary framework first, portability where free | OK | Issue explicitly cites P10 and correctly reasons that skills stay in `.claude/skills/` — pointing other adapters there is the \"portability where free\" path. |\n| Only what's needed | OK | 2-4 lines per file; minimal change solving a concrete gap. |\n| Improve incrementally | OK | Small, self-contained improvement. |\n| A change includes its consequences | Watch | The consequences map says \"If you change a framework skill → also update that framework's adapter file.\" This issue is the reverse: updating adapter files to *reference* skills. No consequence gap, but the implementer should verify the skill list in each adapter stays accurate if skills are added/removed later. Consider whether a comment in the skills directory (or a note in the consequences map) would help keep the references in sync. |\n| Workspace vs. project separation | OK | Workspace infra change; no project-specific content. |\n\n### ADR Applicability\n\n| ADR | Triggered? | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| 0006 — Shared AGENTS.md | Watch | This changes agent instruction files (the adapter files), which is the domain of ADR-0006. The change is consistent with ADR-0006's intent: shared rules in `AGENTS.md`, framework adapters as thin wrappers. Adding a pointer to skills keeps the adapters thin. |\n| 0003 — Project-agnostic workspace | No | Skills are generic workflow procedures, not project-specific. |\n| Others | No | Not triggered by this change type. |\n\n### Consequences\n\n- The consequences map entry for \"A framework skill (e.g., `.claude/skills/`)\" says \"Also update: That framework's adapter file; regenerate skills if needed.\" This issue is essentially fulfilling that consequence entry for non-Claude adapters — good alignment.\n- The issue mentions \"optionally list the available skills by name.\" If the implementation does list them, those lists will need updating when skills are added or removed. Consider whether this maintenance burden is worth the discoverability benefit, or whether a glob instruction (`read .claude/skills/*/SKILL.md`) is more maintainable.\n- The issue body lists 8 workflow skills but the actual `.claude/skills/` directory contains additional `make_*` skills and `brand-guidelines`. The implementation should clarify which skills to reference — likely only the workflow skills (not the `make_*` auto-generated ones), but this should be explicit.\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- **Prefer a glob instruction over an explicit list** in the adapter text (e.g., \"read `.claude/skills/*/SKILL.md`\") to avoid the listed skills going stale as skills are added or removed. If an explicit list is preferred for discoverability, add a note to the consequences map that skill additions should update these three files.\n- **Verify relative paths** from each adapter file to `.claude/skills/`. The Gemini CLI file is at `.agent/instructions/`, Copilot is at `.github/`, and Onboarding is at `.agent/` — each needs a different relative path (or use repo-root-relative paths for clarity).\n- The `brand-guidelines` skill is absent from the issue's list of 8 skills — confirm whether it should be included or excluded in the adapter references.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772202086,"nonce":"L7JrsfWqjRu5ko7R0paSjsUTOOA=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87s0nE5","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/305#issuecomment-3973214521"},"message":"Add the brand guildlines skill. Another issue updates it to move project specific parts to the project","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772210328,"nonce":"cqhni9ss8xsgdScWW4askVVBfmI=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87ufQ8azwAAAAVjU1Y4"},"status":2}]}